{"source_key":"sha256-3639711ec9037118dec0595de2c93477","record_index":1734,"record_hash":"sha256:c9e1ae134480096c7dfa05b4147c75155a9c0b658278d92b1060a3ac729dfb8e","timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:41:29.862Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Findings:\\n\\n- **Fix now: duplicate GitMeta reads in preview hydration.**  \\n  [gitmeta.rs:468](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:468) computes related sessions and already verifies index hits via turn detail reads at [gitmeta.rs:622](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:622). Then preview calls `related_session_detail_from_handle` at [gitmeta.rs:472](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:472), which re-reads the same target index at [gitmeta.rs:657](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:657) and re-verifies turn details at [gitmeta.rs:669](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:669). Use `related.turn_keys` directly and add a helper that hydrates from known verified turn keys.\\n\\n- **Fix now before API exposure: preview reuses repo-private timeline DTOs too broadly.**  \\n  `PreviewReviewSession` exposes `RelatedSession` and `RelatedTimelineTurn` directly at [gitmeta.rs:204](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:204). That leaks internal IDs like `session_key`, `turn_keys`, `source_key`, and record hashes from [gitmeta.rs:184](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:184), [gitmeta.rs:125](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:125), and [gitmeta.rs:1190](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:1190). It also forwards `source_record` at [gitmeta.rs:1201](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:1201). Stored records are redacted, but this is still the wrong boundary for “what would be shared.” Make preview project into a smaller share DTO and omit `source_record`, `record_hash`, and source/internal keys unless the product explicitly needs them.\\n\\n- **Later: transcript hydration scans full transcript lists per previewed session.**  \\n  [gitmeta.rs:755](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:755) reads the whole transcript list, then [gitmeta.rs:790](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:790) scans until all selected hashes are found. Fine for POC/top-3 previews. Don’t add a hash index now unless real sessions get big enough to hurt.\\n\\n- **Ignore: no raw environment leak in the preview payload.**  \\n  `TurnDetail` stores full environment at [gitmeta.rs:90](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:90), but hydrated preview turns only expose `environment_snapshot_status` at [gitmeta.rs:125](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:125). The verification read at [gitmeta.rs:904](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:904) inspects `observed_targets` and returns a bool. That boundary is okay.\\n\\n- **Ignore for now: index-first lookup still verifies every hit before capping.**  \\n  [gitmeta.rs:613](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:613) has to verify candidates to avoid trusting stale/rebuildable indexes, and scoring needs turn counts. Not worth optimizing until target indexes are demonstrably large.\\n\\nNo edits made.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:41:29.862Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}